An Act relative to renewing and expanding the Accelerated Bridge Program.
Whereas, The deferred operation of this act would tend to defeat its purpose, which is to
establish the accelerated bridge program to repair bridges in the commonwealth, therefore it is
hereby declared to be an emergency law, necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
safety.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 29 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting, after
2 Section 2JJJJJJ, the following section:-
3 Section 2KKKKKK. (a) There shall be established and set up on the books of the
4 commonwealth a separate fund, to be known as the Accelerated Bridge Fund. The fund shall: (i)
5 address the specific needs of rural and underserved communities in the commonwealth to
6 ensures equitable distribution of resources; and (ii) prioritize projects in rural areas in order to
7 expedited timelines, additional technical support and dedicated funding to mitigate the
8 disproportionate impact of bridge closures. It shall consist of amounts credited to the fund in
9 accordance with this section. The secretary of the Massachusetts Department of Transportation
1 of 5

10 shall be the custodian of the fund and shall collaborate with local governments in rural areas to
11 identify high-priority projects and streamline the allocation of resources.
12 (b) The fund shall consist of: (i) revenue from appropriations or other money authorized
13 by the general court and specifically designated to be credited to the fund; (ii) interest earned on
14 money in the fund; (iii) federal grants and other gifts, grants and donations; and (iv) the proceeds
15 of bonds issued by the commonwealth. Amounts credited to the fund shall not be subject to
16 further appropriation and any money remaining in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall not
17 revert to the General Fund.
18 (c) Money in the fund shall be expended for the accelerated bridge program established in
19 section 28 of chapter 84 to carry out the goals of the program including, but not limited to: (i) the
20 repairing and replacement of bridges classified as structurally deficient by the Massachusetts
21 Department of Transportation; (ii) preventive maintenance to extend the life of bridges at risk of
22 becoming structurally deficient; (iii) expediting repairs and upgrades in rural and underserved
23 communities to ensure equitable infrastructure investment; and (iv) engineering studies, project
24 design and innovation grants focused on sustainable and resilient bridge construction methods.
25 (d) The fund shall prioritize funding for program projects addressing: (i) bridges with the
26 highest safety risks as determined by Massachusetts Department of Transportation’s bridge
27 inspection program; (ii) structures critical to emergency response routes, economic activity and
28 community connectivity; (iii) projects in rural areas where alternative routes create significant
29 inconvenience or safety concerns; and (iv) regions that have historically received a lower
30 proportion of transportation funding under statewide initiatives.
