36 SECTION 2. Chapter 84 of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the following
37 section:-
38 Section 28. (a) For the purposes of section, the following words shall, unless the context
39 clearly requires otherwise, have the following meanings:
40 “Committee”, the bridge improvement oversight committee.
41 “Department”, the Massachusetts Department of Transportation.
42 “Program”, the accelerated bridge program.
43 (b) There shall be established an accelerated bridge program to reinstate and expand
44 efforts to finance the repair, replacement and maintenance of structurally-deficient bridges across
45 the commonwealth. The program shall address rising infrastructure costs, prioritize equitable
46 investment in rural and underserved areas and leverage federal funding opportunities to ensure
47 statewide transportation safety and economic resilience.
48 (c) There shall be established a bridge improvement oversight committee to monitor the
49 program’s implementation and recommend improvements to the program under this section. The
50 committee shall consist of 5 members: (i) the secretary of department or their designee, who
51 shall serve as chair; (ii) the administrator of the division of highways of the department or their
3 of 5

52 designee; (iii) 1 member appointed by the speaker of the house of representatives, who shall be
53 from a rural community in the commonwealth; (iv) 1 member appointed by the president of the
54 senate, who shall be from a rural community in the commonwealth; and (v) 1 member appointed
55 by the governor, who shall be an independent engineering expert.
56 (d) The program shall be funded by the Accelerated Bridge Fund established in section
57 2KKKKKK of chapter 29.
58 (e) The department shall implement streamlined permitting, contracting and approval
59 processes for the program’s projects to reduce the time required for project initiation and
60 completion. Public-private partnerships and design-build contracts shall be encouraged by the
61 department to accelerate construction timelines while maintaining high standards of safety and
62 quality.
63 (f) The department shall maintain a publicly accessible online portal on its website
64 displaying information on the program’s ongoing and planned projects, including progress
65 updates, project impacts and contact information for public inquiries. The portal shall include a
66 specific section highlighting projects in rural communities.
67 (g) All program projects under this section shall incorporate climate-resilient design
68 principles, minimize environmental impact and comply with applicable state and federal
69 environmental regulations.
70 (h) The committee, in consultation with the department, shall prepare an annual report
71 that shall include: (i) projects funded under this section, including their scope, timeline and cost;
72 (ii) the progress in reducing the number of structurally-deficient bridges in the commonwealth;
73 and (iii) the allocation and expenditure of funds, with specific details on investments in rural
